transcript.content: Hello User! I'm here to get to know you and understand what brought you here today. Tell me—what's going on in your life right now that made you come to Tomorrow You?
I am a finance guy working in JP Morgan in NYC but I am burning out, I am hesitating to move into a cabin in ontario in the woods
That sounds like a big transition — what's making you consider leaving the city and your career behind? And what's your living situation like right now in NYC?
I make a good living but the working hours are daunting and I never get to see my siblings who work over there
Got it — so you're torn between stability and family. What's your income range, roughly? And what's the hardest part about the hours?
I make a good living but the working hours are daunting and I never get to see my siblings who work over there
You're making enough to be comfortable, but the hours are draining you. What's the hardest part about the hours?
I come home at 3 in the morning most days and go to work at 8, I barely sleep
That sounds brutal. What scares you most about making a big change? And how are you actually doing — stress, energy, sleep?
I am doing poorly, sleep deprived and stressed out but I’m afraid I won’t be able to have the same lifestyle if I become a forest guard in Ontario

It sounds like you're torn between your current lifestyle and your well-being, with family ties pulling you toward Ontario. What's really at stake for you in this decision? Is it more about freedom, stability, or something else?
Got it. What does stability mean to you in this context? Is it financial security, routine, or something else?
I see. How do you feel about taking financial risks? Are you someone who prefers to play it safe or are you open to some uncertainty?
I like to keep some uncertainty
Got it. What's the story you tell yourself about why you're still at JP Morgan despite feeling burned out?
